Rating: 3
Excellent one dish meal! One suggestion for making this a little faster/easier clean up: if you can get those soup "bags" (they're made of cheesecloth) then all you have to do it put the whole cilantro (why destem?), ginger, lemongrass, etc into it, tie it up and fish it out after simmering. I tied the smashed coriander seeds into a small piece of doubled-cheesecloth tied with a string, also to be fished out later. That way, all you have to do is pluck it out with tongs, let it cool, squeeze out the excess broth to dump back into the pot and you can skip the straining step. If you can't find the bags then just use cheesecloth and tie it up.

